# Init Node

When initializing a Node.js project:

## Package.json
- Use ES modules: `"type": "module"`
- Include scripts: dev, start, build, test, lint, format
- Keep initialization idempotent

## Structure
```
project/
├── package.json
├── src/
│   └── index.js (entry point)
└── ...
```

## Scripts Template
```json
{
  "type": "module",
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "node --watch src/index.js",
    "start": "node src/index.js",
    "build": "echo 'Build step here'",
    "test": "echo 'Test step here'",
    "lint": "echo 'Lint step here'",
    "format": "echo 'Format step here'"
  }
}
```

## Entry Point
Create `src/index.js`:
```javascript
console.log('Node project initialized');
```
